                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways, Inc./519:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-06T14:00:00-04:30"
                            >July 6, 1929—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>81. Department’s 23, June 13, 7 p.m. Foreign Office informs me that Minister of
                    Fomento states he has been unable to reach an agreement <pb facs="0703" n="567"
                        xml:id="pg_567"/> with the representatives of Pan American Airways regarding
                    provisional permit but that he reiterated “sincere purpose of collaborating as
                    far as possible in the establishment of a fast and efficient mail service
                    between the two countries upon bases beneficial to both.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
